Operators

You can use these SQL operators with calculated insights in Data Cloud.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Edition
Arithmetic Operators

Use these operators to perform arithmetic operations on numeric operands.

Multiply
Add
Subtract
Divide
Logical Operators

Use these logical operators to combine one or more true or false values. The logical operator returns either a true or false value.

FUNCTION	OPERATOR	DATA TYPE
Logical not	!= , <>	Text, URL, Email, Phone, Number, Percent, Date, DateTime
Less than	<	Number, Percent, Date, DateTime
Less than or equal to	<=	Number, Percent, Date, DateTime
Equal to	=	Text, URL, Email, Phone, Number, Percent, Date, DateTime
Greater than	>	Number, Percent, Date, DateTime
Greater than or equal to	>=	Number, Percent, Date, DateTime
And	and	Text, URL, Email, Phone, Number, Percent, Date, DateTime, Boolean
Search for a specified pattern in a column	LIKE; %	Text, URL, Email, Phone
Match a pattern against an expression	RLIKE	Text, URL, Email, Phone
Boolean evaluations	Is_True, Is_False, Has_Boolean_Value, Has_No_Boolean_Value	Boolean
EXAMPLE This example uses logical operators to find individuals who spent more than $5 with a 9 or lower tax rate, an adjusted tax amount that equals 0, and a list price that isn’t $100.
SELECT
SUM(SALESORDER__dlm.grand_total_amount__c) as TotalOrderAmount__c,
Individual__dlm.Id__c as CustomerId__c
FROM SALESORDER__dlm
LEFT JOIN Individual__dlm ON SALESORDER__dlm.partyid__c = Individual__dlm.Id__c
Where SALESORDER__dlm.grand_total_amount__c > 5 and SALESORDER__dlm.tax_rate__c <= 9 and SALESORDER__dlm.total_adjustment_tax_amount__c = 0 and SALESORDER__dlm.list_price__c !=100*
GROUP BY CustomerId__c
Date and Time Operators
Data Cloud exposes several date and type operators for use in your calculated insights SQL expressions.
Boolean Operators
You can use a boolean data type when adding an aggregate function to define a calculated insight SQL statement in Data Cloud. The boolean operator returns either a true or false value as a single byte.
